C085.description:
Common Health Entry Document for Plants and Plant Products (CHED-PP) (as set out in Part 2, Section C of Annex II to Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 2019/1715 (OJ L 261)) The CHED-PP is to be used for the importation of 
- Plants, plant products and other objects referred to in points (c), (d), (e) or (f) of Article 47(1) of Regulation (EU) 2017/625; 
- Specific plants, plant products and other objects of a particular origin or provenance for which a minimum level of official controls is necessary to respond to recognised uniform hazards and risks to plant health as provided for in Implementing Regulation (EU) 2019/66.

9ING.guidance_chief:
- Document Reference: the Ingredient code;

- Quantity: enter the quantity of the ingredient expressed in Kilograms.

- Note: No status code (as contained in document status codes for harmonised declarations) is required.
